name: Warung D' Carik Nyalian
address: Jl. Raya Desa Nyalian, Nyalian, Kec. Banjarangkan, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80752, Indonesia
review 1: Nice place to relax in a rice field while enjoying some local snacks. The Balinese cakes are great and the iced lemon tea was very fresh. Prices are reasonable and service was good. Only recommendation would be to tidy up a bit more as some guests had thrown rubbish on the ground and it was not cleaned up by staff.
review 2:

The hospitality was exceptional and the food was sooooo good!

review 4: Hidden service fee and tax fee, those are additionaly added to the price but not visible anywhere on the menu price list. That is not the practice of other restaurants on Bali that we visited. Laklak (green balinase cake) had burnt taste (we could not eat it). Otherwise the place has potential since surrounding is very nice
review 5: Simply amazing traditional food. Priced right. We could not fault this place. Whether local or a tourist its a must. Great friendly service. Thank you to all and to Dewa the owner. Bangga tentu saja! Be proud for sure!
